{{Spanish name|Fontana|Lázaro}} {{Infobox scientist | name = Josep Fontana | image = El historiador Josep Fontana (cropped).jpg | caption = Josep Fontana in 2017 | birth_name = Josep Fontana i Lázaro | birth_date = {{birth date|1931|11|20}} | birth_place = [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]] | death_date = {{death date and age |2018|08|28|1931|11|20}} | death_place = Barcelona, Catalonia | fields = [[History]] | alma_mater = [[Universidad de Barcelona]] | doctoral_students = Roberto Fernández Díaz | influenced = {{hlist|[[Jaume Vicens i Vives]]|Ferran Soldevila Zubiburu}} | awards = [[Creu de Sant Jordi]] }}
'''Josep Fontana i Lázaro''' (20 November 1931 &ndash; 28 August 2018) was a Spanish historian from [[Catalonia]].<ref name="La">{{cite news |url=http://www.lavanguardia.es:80/premium/publica/publica?COMPID=51369747724&ID_PAGINA=22088&ID_FORMATO=9&turbourl=false |title=Josep Fontana recibe el Premi Nacional de Cultura de la Generalitat por su trayectoria profesional |newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]] |date=5 July 2007 |access-date=30 August 2018 |location=Barcelona |language=es |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20080515021310/http://www.lavanguardia.es:80/premium/publica/publica?COMPID=51369747724&ID_PAGINA=22088&ID_FORMATO=9&turbourl=false |archive-date=15 May 2008}}</ref><ref name="El">{{cite news |url=https://elpais.com/diario/2008/06/04/catalunya/1212541660_850215.html |title=Josep Fontana dona 37.000 libros y documentos a la Universidad Pompeu Fabra |newspaper=[[El Pais]] |first=Verónica |last=Sánchez Orpella |date=4 June 2008 |access-date=30 August 2018 |location=Barcelona |language=es}}</ref>
==Education== Born in Barcelona, he received his [[master's degree]] in philosophy and letters (section history) at the [[University of Barcelona]] in 1956 and his [[doctorate]] in history by the same university in 1970. He was a student of [[Jaume Vicens i Vives]] and [[Ferran Soldevila]]. Their main currents of investigation are [[economic history]], 19th century [[History of Spain|Spanish history]] and the history of property. He has been influenced in his thought by [[E.P. Thompson]], [[Pierre Vilar]], [[Gramsci]] and [[Walter Benjamin]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.hoy.es/20080408/local/prov-badajoz/josep-fontana-analizara-transicion-200804081241.html |title=Josep Fontana analizará la Transición Española en una conferencia en Zafra |magazine=Hoy |author=Europa Press |author-link=Europa Press (news agency) |date=8 April 2008 |access-date=30 August 2018 |language=es}}</ref>
==Career== The Jaume Vicens i Vives University Institute of History, the interdisciplinary Ph.D. history institute in the [[Pompeu Fabra University]] in Barcelona was originally directed and founded by Dr. Fontana, in which he continues to teach classes of Introduction to History and 20th-century Spanish history. He has taught economic, the interplay between history, law and economics and contemporary history at the [[University of Barcelona]], the [[University of Valencia]] and at the [[Autonomous University of Barcelona]].<ref name="La" />
Dr. Fontana has been an active contributor to scholarly history publications since 1970, among them, ''l'Avenç'' (1976). The Introduction to History course taught during the first cycle of the [[humanities]] track of the [[Universitat Pompeu Fabra]] is based on Fontana's book ''Introduction to the Study of History''.<ref name="La" /><ref name="El" />
==Publications== *1971: ''La quiebra de la monarquía absoluta (1814-1820)'' (Crítica) *1979: ''La crisis del Antiguo Régimen'' (Crítica) *1982: ''Historia: análisis del pasado y proyecto social'' (Crítica) *1992: ''La història després de la fi de la història'' (Eumo) *1994: ''Europa ante el espejo'' (Crítica) *1999: ''Enseñar historia con una guerra civil de por medio'' (Crítica) *1999: ''Introducció a l'estudi de la història'' (Crítica) *2000: ''La història dels homes'' (Crítica) *2005: ''Aturar el temps'' (Crítica) *2006: ''De en medio del tiempo'' (Crítica) *2006: ''La construcció de la identitat'' (Base) *2007: ''Historia de España, vol. 6: La época del liberalismo'' (Crítica-Marcial Pons) *2010: ''L'ofici d'historiador'' (Documenta Universitària) *2011: ''Por el bien del imperio. Una historia del mundo desde 1945'' (Pasado & Presente) *2013: ''El futuro es un país extraño. Una reflexión sobre la crisis social de comienzos de siglo'' (Pasado & Presente)
