{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox school | name = Walden's Path - The Magnet School | image = The_Magnet_School_logo.jpg | size = 290px | caption = Awakening Intelligence | established = 2015 | schooltype = Progressive School | gender = Co-educational | founder = Sunil Mayreddy<ref>{{cite web|title=Founder|url=https://www.magnetschool.edu.in/about/|website=magnetschool.edu.in|accessdate=28 April 2016}}</ref> | sister_school = [[Walden's Path]] | city = [[Hyderabad]] | state = [[Telangana]] | country = [[India]] | website = {{URL|https://www.magnetschool.edu.in}} }} '''Walden's Path | The Magnet School'''<ref>{{cite web|title=The Magnet School|url=https://www.magnetschool.edu.in/|website=Magnet School|publisher=The Magnet School|accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref> is a K-12 Progressive School in [[Hyderabad]], [[India]] that is inspired by the philosophy and views on education of [[Jiddu Krishnamurti]]. The school is managed by the Walden Education Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Walden Education Foundation|url=http://www.corpdir.in/1606642-walden-education-foundation/basic.html|website=corpdir.in|publisher=corpdir|accessdate=22 February 2016}}</ref> The Magnet School follows 'The Studio Approach' with Science, Mathematics, Language and Literature. The Magnet School developed an approach and methodology that enables children to discover multiple ways of solving problems in Mathematics and applying concepts in Science.<ref>{{cite news|title=AN INTERESTING PATH TO TAKE...|url=http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31809&articlexml=AN-INTERESTING-PATH-TO-TAKE-17042015452026#|accessdate=17 April 2015|issue=Times School|publisher=Times Of India|date=17 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Our Approach|url=https://www.magnetschool.edu.in/approach/|website=The Magnet School|publisher=The Magnet School|accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref>
==Studio-based learning== Walden's Path | The Magnet School follows Studio Based Learning developed by John Dewey. Unlike a lab that uses standardised procedures with set equipment to reproduce a protocol in order to obtain set outcomes, a Studio is a space that invigorates, inspires and provides an opportunity to create, construct and test objectives and hypotheses and analyse data.<ref>{{cite web|title=Studio Based Learning|url=https://www.magnetschool.edu.in/studio-based-learning/|website=www.magnetschool.edu.in|publisher=The Magnet School|accessdate=12 July 2015}}</ref>
At The Magnet School, The Experiential Studio serves grades 1 - IV while The Scholar’s Studio serves grades V - XII.
